Representative Charlie Gonzalez, who has served in the United States House of Representatives for the past 50 years alongside his father, has announced his retirement. During his time in Congress, Gonzalez has been a strong advocate for environmental preservation, Wall Street reform, and improved healthcare access for Texans. He has also served as Chair of the Congressional Hispanic Caucus, working to support immigrant families and protect the civil rights of Latinos and all Americans. President Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama extend their best wishes to Gonzalez and his family, thanking him for his dedicated service to the people of Texas.